hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Recorded Delivery orjinal femore jel As the pounds were coming on, I was learning that I had fears I wasn't aware of. I was afraid that I would be judged based on what I looked like. And I learned that I was judging myself when I would look in the mirror, and I would create this idea around: No one will love me this way. I always had this idea that, "Oh my gosh, everyone should look more inside because that's what it's all about." But I discovered that I was just as guilty as the next person of being obsessed with my external appearance.
